…Over the past 14 years, I’ve had the PRIVILEGE to travel the world many times over as a Producer, showcasing BEATS for adoring crowds in amazing venues. It’s been the experience of a LIFETIME. So, in 2018, I wanted to start sharing that experience with other INCREDIBLE beatmakers around the world, by starting an ANNUAL Producer Tour called “BEAT LIFE”.

The basic idea behind “Beat Life” was to invite other AMAZING Producers to join me on the road, ultimately to give the BEAT LOVING COMMUNITY more of a show, and more of a good time, but also to expose other Producers to my own beneficial experiences and lasting connections, domestic and abroad. Whether you’re a legend, or up-and-coming, we can all learn from eachother, and have fun doing so.

“Beat Life” obviously came to a screeching halt in 2020 when the Pandemic made it’s interruption, but we’re FINALLY BACK at it with the next installment!

“Beat Life III” featuring STU BANGAS!

I don’t think I have to go into this man’s WORK too much, do I? He’s produced for the likes of Vinnie Paz, Method Man, Eric Bobo, Ill Bill, Pharoahe Monch, Apathy, Cappadonna, Blacastan(RIP), RJ Payne, Recognize Ali, & Chino XL, just to name a few.

You know his music, you know what kind of beats he makes, you DEFINITELY know my music, and you know this tour is gonna be a CRAZY time! If you’re in any one of these cities, come out and get these HEAD NODS! 🥁 LET’S GO! #BeatLifeTour #ApolloBrown #StuBangas #MindFeederz

…Tonight in Bologna, Italy, is the LAST stop of the 2023 Beat Life III Tour! It’s the GRAND FINALE, so let’s make this one special! 🥁 I want to give a big THANK YOU to my guy @Stu_Bangas for joining me on this installment. Appreciate you brotha! 🙏🏽 Your BEATS are straight MURDER for this type of tour, and it’s been a pleasure to rock along side you. 💥 Yo, and I was just thinking. The fact that I can travel all over the world and JUST play my BEATS for fans and supporters, without having to rely on an Emcee counterpart(although I LOVE traveling with Emcees), has been a blessing for the last 13 years on the road. 🌍 Not many beat-makers can do that. So, I’m thankful for all of the opportunities I’ve been able to experience as a Producer. 🪄 I have to say though, NONE of my globetrotting would be possible without my FAMILY, @TheMindFeederz. Timm, you’re my Brother. You always got my back, and I appreciate you wholeheartedly. Cheers to the years ahead. 🍻 Anyway, Balogna, come on out tonight so we can crack some heads one last time! Let’s go! #BeatLifeTour #ApolloBrown #StuBangas #MindFeederz

…Everybody knows that as an emcee, Planet Asia is not only one of the BEST to do it, but one of MY personal favorites to adorn the mic. That being said, we just HAD to follow up the cult-like showing of “Anchovies”, with the second offering, appropriately titled, “Sardines”. And just like a can of Anchovies ISN’T for everyone, the SAME can be said about a tin full of Sardines. You either love’em or you hate’em. 🤷🏽‍♂️ This album had to be done, and in my opinion, done BETTER than the first. Dirt, grit, mud, sticks & stones, all that. Leave your boots on. 🥾 

The NEW joint “Get The Dough Off” gives you a glimpse of what the Sardines album is about lyrically, sonically, and conceptually. It’s the PERFECT way to open the tin can. Smell it. We’ve BEEN doing this. “…it’s for the 20 year fiends”. Go check it out NOW! Link in Bio. 🎣 #Sardines #ApolloBrown #PlanetAsia #MelloMusicGroup

…welp, “Chevelle Season” is now over for me, indefinitely. It’s the end of an era. For those that know me, you know how I felt about that car. It was a labor of love. A decade of blood, sweat, tears, and money. Despite it all though, I decided it was time to move on and let someone else enjoy it. It was absolutely bittersweet watching the Chevelle be hauled off, but I know it definitely went to a good home. Now, it’s time for a new chapter in my car life. 🤔 My Wife says I’m going through a midlife crisis. That may be so, lol, but I’ll take it. Stay tuned for what’s next! 🏁
